<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Margin affects left floated elements</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visuren.html#floats" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Right outer edge of left-floating box cannot be to the right of the left outer edge of any right-floating box that is to the right of it." />
        <style type="text/css">* { margin: 0; padding: 0 }
            div
            {
                border: solid 5px black;
                height: 2in;
                width: 2in;
            }
            span
            {
                height: 1in;
                width: 1in;
            }
            #span1
            {
                background: blue;
                float: left;
                margin-right: 10px;
            }
            #span2
            {
                background-color: orange;
                float: right;
                margin-left: 10px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the blue box is aligned on the left side of the black box and is above the orange, right aligned, box.</p>
        <div>
            <span id="span1"></span>
            <span id="span2"></span>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>